==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Flat-cap
<hw>Flat"-cap`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A kind of
low-crowned cap formerly worn by all classes in England, and continued
in London after disuse elsewhere; -- hence, a citizen of London.</def>
<rj><au>Marston.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

